cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the detection and decomposition of shapes in natural images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The use of clustering and optimization techniques also suggests cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves the use of encoding and inversion techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, indicating cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. Finally, the use of weighted geometric set cover problem suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
